      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hey! For your 12-stop delivery loop, the best mathematical approach is the **Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP)** solved with a **dynamic programming algorithm** (the Held–Karp method).  \nHere’s the quick rundown:\n\n1. **Model the problem**  \n   - Let \\(V = \\{1,2,\\dots,12\\}\\) be the set of stops.  \n   - Define a distance matrix \\(D = [d_{ij}]\\) where \\(d_{ij}\\) is the mileage between stop \\(i\\) and stop \\(j\\).  \n   - You want a permutation \\(\\pi\\) of \\(V\\) that minimizes  \n     \\[\n     \\sum_{k=0}^{11} d_{\\pi(k),\\,\\pi(k+1)} + d_{\\pi(11),\\,\\pi(0)}\n     \\]\n     (the last term closes the loop).\n\n2. **Use the Held–Karp DP**  \n   - Let \\(T(S,i)\\) be the minimum cost of a path that starts at a fixed depot, visits all nodes in subset \\(S\\), and ends at node \\(i",
